        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:36PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 335 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Stevenson, or 8 miles south of Bridgeport, moving
north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bridgeport, Stevenson, Fabius, Higdon, Long Island, and Russell Cave
National Monument.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
